Top-Level Domains
    ex) .com, .net, etc

Second-Level Domains
    ex) www.google.com - 2nd level domain would be google.
        www.yahoo.com  - 2nd level domain would be yahoo.

Subdomain
    ex) www.google.com - Subdomain would be www
        www.whatever.com - Subdomain would be www

Route53 is always 100% available.
    Services
        Domain Registrations

            Authority that can assign domains under a top
            level domain. (There domains are registered with InterNIC)
        
        DNS Routing
        Health Checks

    Hosted Zones - containers for records 
    that determine how traffic is routed
    for domains and subdomains

        Public Hosted Zone - records for routing traffic
        on the public internet.

        Private Hosted Zones - Records for routing
        traffic within a VPC.6

Components of record
    Domain and Subdomain
    Record Type: A, CNAME, MX, NS, SOA
        A Records - Routing traffic to IPv4 address
        AAAA Records - Routing to IPv6 address
        NS Record - Identifies the name servers for the hosted zone
        Alias - Record that routes traffic to specific AWS resources

    IP or hostname traffic is being routed to.
    Policy associated with the record
    TTL value - Number of seconds to cache values

    
